In [65]:
def outlier_method(df, variable_name):
    outlier=[]
    lower=int(df[variable_name].quantile(0.25))
    upper=int(df[variable_name].quantile(0.75))
    iqr=upper-lower
    lower_range=int(lower-1.5*iqr)
    upper_range=int(upper+1.5*iqr)
    print('The range of is ',lower_range,"-",upper_range)
    for p in df[variable_name]:
        if p not in range(lower_range,upper_range+1):
            outlier.append(p)
    return outlier
In [66]:
def outlier_treat(df,col,outliers):
    lower=df[col].quantile(0.10)
    upper=df[col].quantile(0.90)
    df[col]=np.where(df[col]<lower,lower,df[col])
    df[col]=np.where(df[col]>upper,upper,df[col])
    return df
